er translations of Wundt's publications are of a highly questionable reliability.\n* [http://psychclassics.yorku.ca/Wundt/Physio/ ''Principles of Physiological Psychology'']\n* [http://psychclassics.yorku.ca/Wundt/Outlines/index.htm ''Outlines of Psychology'']\n* ''Ethics: An Investigation of the Facts and Laws of the Moral Life''. Volume 1. (Tr. [[Edward B. Titchener]] ''et al.''.) <small>Second Edition, 1902.</small> [https://archive.org/details/ethicsaninvesti01wundgoog University of Michigan].\n* ''Lectures on Human and Animal Psychology''. (Trs. [[Edward B. Titchener]] and James E. Creighton.) <small>Second Edition, 1896.</small> [https://archive.org/details/lecturesonhuman02wundgoog Harvard].<small>Fourth Edition, 1907.</small> [https://archive.org/details/lecturesonhuman01wundgoog Stanford]; [https://archive.org/details/lecturesonhumana00wundiala UCLA]; [https://archive.org/details/lecturesonhumana00wund University of Illinois].\n* ''Outlines of Psychology''. (Tr. [[Charles Hubbard Judd]].) <small>Second Edition, 1902.</small> [https://archive.org/details/outlinespsychol00juddgoog Stanford].\n* ''Principles of Physiological Psychology''. Volume 1. (Tr. [[Edward B. Titchener]].)<small>First Edition, 1904.</small> [https://books.google.com/books?id=b48RAAAAYAAJ Harvard]; [https://archive.org/details/principlesphysi01wundgoog Lane]; [https://books.google.com/books?id=p_IMAAAAIAAJ University of Michigan]; [http://psychclassics.yorku.ca/Wundt/Physio/ HTML]. <small>Second Edition, 1910.</small> [https://archive.org/details/principlesofphys00wundiala UCLA].\n\n{{Psychology}}\n{{Philosophy of science}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Wundt, Wilhelm}}\n[[Category:1832 births]]\n[[Category:1920 deaths]]\n[[Category:People from Mannheim]]\n[[Category:German psychologists]]\n[[Category:Experimental psychologists]]\n[[Category:19th-century psychologists]]\n[[Category:20th-century psychologists]]\n[[Category:People from the Grand Duchy of Baden]]\n[[Category:University of T\u00fcbingen alumni]]\n[[Category:Humboldt University of Berlin alumni]]\n[[Category:Heidelberg University alumni]]\n[[Category:Heidelberg University faculty]]\n[[Category:Leipzig University faculty]]\n[[Category:Rectors of Leipzig University]]\n[[Category:Philosophers of science]]\n[[Category:Foreign associates of the National Academy of Sciences]]\n[[Category:Honorary Members of the St Petersburg Academy of Sciences]]\n[[Category:Members of the Second Chamber of the Diet of the Grand Duchy of Baden]]\n[[Category:Members of the Bavarian Maximilian Order for Science and Art]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Pour le M\u00e9rite (civil class)]]\n", "name_user": "Regionsofsorrow", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eBooks and articles", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wilhelm_Wundt"}
{"title_page": "2020 STCC TCR Scandinavia Touring Car Championship", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{One source|date=November 2019}}\n{{Motorsport season\n|series=STCC TCR Scandinavia Touring Car Championship\n|link=STCC TCR Scandinavia Touring Car Championship\n|year=2020\n|previouslink = 2019 TCR Scandinavia Touring Car Championship\n|previoussuffix = [[TCR Scandinavia Touring Car Championship|TCR Scandinavia]]\n|footer=\n}}\n\n[[File:Robert Dahlgren 2016-04-30 003.png|thumb|upright=0.7|[[Robert Dahlgren]] is the reigning Drivers' Champion.]]\n\nThe '''2020 STCC TCR Scandinavia Touring Car Championship''' is a planned regional motor racing championship for [[TCR Touring Car|TCR]] touring cars which would be the fourth year of running with TCR regulations. It'll be the second time the championship has run under the [[STCC TCR Scandinavia Touring Car Championship]] banner.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.touringcartimes.com/2019/10/05/tcr-scandinavia-targeting-24-car-grid-will-rename-back-stcc/ |title=TCR Scandinavia targeting 24-car grid, and will rename back to STCC |last=Hudson |first=Neil |date=5 October 2019 |publisher=TouringCarTimes |access-date=17 October 2019}}</ref> The season was due to start on 15 May at [[Ring Knutstorp]] and end on 4 October at [[Mantorp Park]], however a revised calendar due to the 2019-2020 coronavirus pandemic is due to be published after Easter. <ref name=\"calendarandpromoter\">{{cite web |url=https://www.touringcartimes.com/2019/10/04/tcr-scandinavia-unveils-new-calendar-promoter-2020/ |title=TCR Scandinavia unveils new calendar and promoter for 2020 |last=Hudson |first=Neil |date=4 October 2019 |publisher=TouringCarTimes |access-date=17 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n[[Robert Dahlgren]] and [[Brink Motorsport]] are the reigning Drivers' and Teams' champions respectively.<!--STCC TCR Scandinavia (or, as it was known as in 2019, TCR Scandinavia) is considered to be a completely separate entity from the defunct TCR Scandinavia that ran between 2010 and 2018, so please don't change this.--><ref name=\"champions\">{{cite web |url=https://www.touringcartimes.com/2019/10/05/andreas-wernersson-wins-final-race-dahlgren-takes-title/ |title=Andreas Wernersson wins final race, Dahlgren takes title |last=Hudson |first=Neil |date=5 October 2019 |publisher=TouringCarTimes |access-date=17 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Entrants ==\nThe following teams and drivers are set to compete in the 2020 season:\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 85%;\"\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"|Entrant\n! rowspan=\"2\"|Car\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"4\"|Race drivers\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"|No.\n! scope=\"col\"|Driver name\n! scope=\"col\"|Rounds\n! scope=\"col\"|{{abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"3\"|{{flagicon|SWE}} Brink Motorsport\n| scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"3\"|[[Audi RS 3|Audi RS 3 LMS TCR]]\n| style=\"text-align:center\"|TBA\n| {{flagicon|SWE}} Hannes Morin\n| TBA\n| align=\"center\"|<ref name=\"BrinkHannes2020\">{{cite web |url=https://www.touringcartimes.com/2020/01/08/brink-motorsport-re-sign-hannes-morin-2020-season/ |title=Brink Motorsport re-sign Hannes Morin for the 2020 season |author=TouringCarTimes |date=8 January 2020 |publisher=TouringCarTimes |access-date=10 January 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| TBA\n| {{flagicon|SWE}} Fredrik Blomstedt\n| TBA\n| align=\"center\"|<ref name=\"BrinkBlomstedt2020\">{{cite web |url=https://www.touringcartimes.com/2020/02/04/fredrik-blomstedt-makes-stcc-return-brink-motorsport/|title=Fredrik Blomstedt makes STCC return with Brink Motorsport|author=TouringCarTimes|date=4 February 2020|publisher=TouringCarTimes |access-date=4 February 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| TBA\n| {{flagicon|SWE}} Tobias Brink\n| TBA\n| align=\"center\"|<ref name=\"TobiasBrink2020\">{{cite web|url=https://www.touringcartimes.com/2020/03/05/tobias-brink-completes-brink-motorsport-line/|title=Tobias Brink completes Brink Motorsport line-up|author=TouringCarTimes|date=5 March 2020|publisher=TouringCarTimes|access-date=9 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flagicon|SWE}} Brovallen Design\n| [[Audi RS 3|Audi RS 3 LMS TCR]]\n| style=\"text-align:center\"|TBA\n| {{flagicon|NOR}} Magnus Gustavsen\n| TBA\n| align=\"center\"|<ref name=\"Brovallen2020\">{{cite web |url=https://www.touringcartimes.com/2020/03/27/magnus-gustavsen-signs-brovallen-design/|title=Magnus Gustavsen signs for Brovallen Design|author=TouringCarTimes|date=27 March 2020|publisher=TouringCarTimes|access-date=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flagicon|SWE}} Experion Racing Team\n| [[Hyundai i30#Third generation .282016.E2.80.93present.29|Hyundai i30 N TCR]]\n| style=\"text-align:center\"|TBA\n| {{flagicon|SWE}} Albin W\u00e4rnel\u00f6v\n| TBA\n| align=\"center\"|<ref name=\"W\u00e4rnel\u00f6v2020\">{{cite web |url=https://www.touringcartimes.com/2020/01/29/experion-racing-announce-switch-volkswagen-hyundai/ |title=Experion Racing announce switch from Volkswagen to Hyundai |author=TouringCarTimes |date=29 January 2020 |publisher=TouringCarTimes |access-date=29 January 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"3\"|{{flagicon|SWE}} K\u00e5gered Racing\n| scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"3\"|[[Volkswagen Golf Mk7#Golf GTI|Volkswagen Golf GTI TCR]]\n| style=\"text-align:center\"| TBA\n| {{flagicon|SWE}} Emil Persson\n| TBA\n| align=\"center\"|<ref name=\"K\u00e5gered2020\">{{cite web |url=https://www.touringcartimes.com/2020/01/20/kagered-racing-confirm-three-cars-2020-stcc-season/ |title=K\u00e5gered Racing confirm three cars for 2020 STCC season |author=TouringCarTimes |date=20 January 2020 |publisher=TouringCarTimes |access-date=21 January 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center\"| TBA\n| {{flagicon|SWE}} Mikael Karlsson\n| TBA\n| align=\"center\"|<ref name=\"K\u00e5gered2020\" />\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center\"| TBA\n| {{flagicon|SWE}} Andreas Ahlberg\n| TBA\n| align=\"center\"|<ref name=\"Ahlberg2020\">{{cite web |url=https://www.touringcartimes.com/2020/03/25/andreas-ahlberg-completes-kagered-racing-line/ 